result.name: Kowloon Bay International Trade & Exhibition Centre

reviews.text: A big mall with conference facilities. Shops on the L1 and B1 levels offer some discount, but not quite the outlet level. Conference rooms and exhibition halls are a bit rundown. The free shuttle bus service to and from the Kowloon Bay MTR station is convenient.

I came here for miku expo and the place is too small for long queues so people have to wait outside with the hot weather but there are legit plenty more space indoor. I know it might not be the mall's fault but idk. Also, the fast food there is slow due to shortage of workers. If there are events holding here, be sure to come here earlier or just eat somewhere else

The Cinema - Metroplex - locates on ground floor of Kowloon Bay International Trade & Exhibition Center (KITEC) is super nice. Excellent sound effect of the theaters, comfortable seats. 
KITEC is also a place for factory outlets and many nice restaurants

The Center provides a very large second hand car show in basement, some outlet stores of famous brands, cinema, indoor bowling Center, restaurants, cafes, supermarket, furniture and fixtures stores.  Besides, it will organise events regularly.  
There is free shuttle bus travelling to & from Telford Plaza.  Free parking will be offered when you purchase goods over the specified amount of money.
I used to go to the restaurant on the top of the building as it is large with plenty of seats.  Easy to get a seat even on a busy holiday.  More important is that the panoramic view from the restaurant is really good, the environment is comfortable and the food quality is good.
The place here is not large enough, ifc is better
